      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Yes. There are serval HiDPI issues on Linux. But IMO its mostly a upstream Qt issue. HiDPI works fine on mac and it should also work fine on Linux and Win (if Qts HiDPI behavior would be platform independent). I strongly discourage from adding linux specific HiDPI fixes (especially #ifdefs!). Well, there are some things like font size definitions which should/could be changed to allow more flexible size calculations (like https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/5898).\n\nI have a Linux/Ubuntu HiDPI setup ready and i'd like to test soon a bitcoin-qt with Qt5.4. If there are still things on \"our side\" to cure, i'd like to see them fixed together in on PR.\n",
